        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-29T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-29T13:00:00-05:00" n="1115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.801/9–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-29T13:00:00-05:00">September 29, 1949—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3545. At request Dept, Brit Emb last week requested FonOff to tele copy Brit
                    protest re Chi Nat Govt seizure SS <hi rend="italic">Edith Moller</hi>
                    ex-Shanghai. Nats have now intercepted three Amer-flag Isbrandtsen ships outside
                    Shanghai. In view desirability knowing Brit line of action, pls indicate FonOff
                    urgency our interest this question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
